com.hazelcast.map.impl.mapstore.writebehind

Class WriteBehindStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.map.impl.mapstore.AbstractMapDataStore<Data,Object>
      • com.hazelcast.map.impl.mapstore.writebehind.WriteBehindStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MapDataStore<Data,Object>

    public class WriteBehindStore
extends AbstractMapDataStore<Data,Object>
    Write behind map data store implementation. Created per every record-store. Only called from one thread.

      • loadAll

        public Map loadAll(Collection keys)
        Loads values for the provided keys if a MapLoader is configured for this map. This method never returns null. The returned map will contain deserialised keys and values. The method first checks if some of the keys to be loaded have entries that are staged to be persisted to the underlying store and returns those values instead of loading the values from the store. The keys which don't have staged entries to be persisted will be loaded from the underlying store.
        Specified by:
        loadAll in interface MapDataStore<Data,Object>
        Overrides:
        loadAll in class AbstractMapDataStore<Data,Object>
        Parameters:
        keys - the keys for which values are loaded
        Returns:
        the map from deserialised key to deserialised value
        See Also:
        MapLoader.loadAll(Collection)

      • loadable

        public boolean loadable(Data key)
        Description copied from interface: MapDataStore
        Used in IMap.loadAll(boolean) calls. If the write-behind map-store feature is enabled, some things may lead to possible data inconsistencies. These are: - calling evict/evictAll, - calling remove, and - not yet stored write-behind queue operations.

        With this method, we can be sure if a key can be loadable from map-store or not.

        Parameters:
        key - the key to query whether it is loadable or not
        Returns:
        true if the key is loadable

      • softFlush

        public long softFlush()
        Description copied from interface: MapDataStore
        Only marks this MapDataStore as flush-able. Flush means storing entries from write-behind-queue into map-store regardless of the scheduled store-time. Actual flushing is done by another thread than partition-operation thread which runs StoreWorker.
        Returns:
        last given sequence number to the last store operation
        See Also:
        MapFlushOperation

      • hardFlush

        public void hardFlush()
        Description copied from interface: MapDataStore
        Flushes write-behind-queue into map-store in calling thread.

        After calling of this method, all elements in the WriteBehindQueue of this MapDataStore should be in map-store regardless of the scheduled store-time.

        The only call to this method is in node-shutdown.

        See Also:
        MapManagedService.shutdown(boolean)
